te through possible values of A and B to find the pair that satisfies both equations\r\npossible_pairs = [(a, 10//a) for a in range(1, 11) if 10 % a == 0]\r\n\r\n# Check which pair satisfies 3A - 8B = -1\r\nsolution_pair = None\r\nfor A, B in possible_pairs:\r\n    if 3*A - 8*B == -1:\r\n        solution_pair = (A, B)\r\n        break\r\n\r\nprint(solution_pair)\n```\n```output\n(2, 5)\n```\nUpon rechecking, the pair \\((A, B) = (2, 5)\\) still does not satisfy \\(3A - 8B = -1\\). Let's manually verify the possible pairs again:\n\nPossible pairs \\((A, B)\\) such that \\(AB = 10\\):\n- \\((1, 10)\\)\n- \\((2, 5)\\)\n- \\((5, 2)\\)\n- \\((10, 1)\\)\n\nChecking each pair:\n1. For \\((1, 10)\\):\n   \\[\n   3 \\cdot 1 - 8 \\cdot 10 = 3 - 80 = -77 \\neq -1\n   \\]\n2. For \\((2, 5)\\):\n   \\[\n   3 \\cdot 2 - 8 \\cdot 5 = 6 - 40 = -34 \\neq -1\n   \\]\n3. For \\((5, 2)\\):\n   \\[\n   3 \\cdot 5 - 8 \\cdot 2 = 15 - 16 = -1 \\quad \\text{(Correct)}\n   \\]\n4. For \\((10, 1)\\):\n   \\[\n   3 \\cdot 10 - 8 \\cdot 1 = 30 - 8 = 22 \\neq -1\n   \\]\n\nSo the correct pair is \\((5, 2)\\). Now we compute \\(AB + B\\):\n\\[\nAB + B = 5 \\cdot 2 + 2 = 10 + 2 = 12\n\\]\n\nThus, the final answer is:\n\\[\n\\boxed{12}\n\\]\n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\n"[0m
