[32m'Masked text for sample 2, segment 3049-3473: ).\n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\nTo determine whether the given answer is correct, we can use the AM-HM inequality, which is a specific case of the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality. The AM-HM inequality states that for positive real numbers \\( x_1, x_2, \\ldots, x_n \\),\n\n\\[\n\\frac{x_1 + x_2 + \\cdots + x_n}{n} \\geq \\frac{n}{\\frac{1}{x_1} + \\frac{1}{x_2} + \\cdots + \\frac{1}{x_n}}\n\\]\n\nApplying this to the problem, we have:\n\n\\[\n\\frac{a + b + c + d}{4} \\geq \\frac{4}{\\frac{1}{a} + \\frac{1}{b} + \\frac{1}{c} + \\frac{1}{d}}\n\\]\n\nMultiplying both sides by 4 and rearranging gives:\n\n\\[\n(a + b + c + d) \\left( \\frac{1}{a} + \\frac{1}{b} + \\frac{1}{c} + \\frac{1}{d} \\right) \\geq 16\n\\]\n\nThe equality condition for the AM-HM inequality occurs when \\( a = b = c = d \\). If we set \\( a = b = c = d = x \\), then:\n\n\\[\n(a + b + c + d) = 4x \\quad \\text{and} \\quad \\frac{1}{a} + \\frac{1}{b} + \\frac{1}{c} + \\frac{1}{d} = \\frac{4}{x}\n\\]\n\nThus, the expression becomes:\n\n\\[\n(4x) \\left( \\frac{4}{x} \\right) = 16\n\\]\n\nTherefore, the minimum value of the expression is indeed 16, and the given answer is correct.<|im_end|>\n'[0m
