ction value at \\( n = a \\) must all be equal. Specifically, we need:\n\n1. \\(\\lim_{n \\to a^-} f(n) = \\lim_{n \\to a^+} f(n)\\)\n2. \\(f(a) = \\lim_{n \\to a} f(n)\\)\n\nGiven the function:\n\n- For \\( n < a \\), \\( f(n) = 4n + 3 \\)\n- For \\( n \\ge a \\), \\( f(n) = 7n - 12 \\)\n\nWe need to set the two expressions equal at \\( n = a \\) to ensure continuity:\n\n\\[ 4a + 3 = 7a - 12 \\]\n\nSolving this equation will confirm whether the given answer \\( a = 5 \\) is correct. \n\nRearranging the equation:\n\n\\[ 4a + 3 = 7a - 12 \\]\n\\[ 3 + 12 = 7a - 4a \\]\n\\[ 15 = 3a \\]\n\\[ a = 5 \\]\n\nThe calculation confirms that the value \\( a = 5 \\) satisfies the condition for continuity of the function \\( f(n) \\). Therefore, the given answer is correct.<|im_end|>\n"[0m
